A11. Discover 5 unique access control devices.
1. Password lock in Reid Librery - In a locker room on ground floor, the locker has a pinpad password lock. To use you put a password in and then press enter, it will lock. Repeat the process with the same password again to unlock.
2. Rotating combination lock box - In front of unigame club room there a locked box that contain a key for the door. It locked with rotation password lock.
3. Authenticator app - This application connect with many other microsoft apps like microsoft team. When you try to sign in it will ask for a number on the app and you have to enter correct number to login.
4. Magic link authentication - This password less login method that will sent you a link in email. When you click on the link it will led you to password changing page. 
5. Buzz For Entry - This device include a camara, speaker, and button. When you click the button you can talk to the security, and they can decide weather or not you can enter.
